: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">including</=
a>=C2=A0traditional financial firms like BlackRock and Fidelity=C2=A0=E2=80=
=94=C2=A0will be able to hold Bitcoins in a pot, and institutional and reta=
il investors will be able to buy and sell shares of that pot to get exposur=
e to Bitcoin=E2=80=99s price without actually owning Bitcoin. This, it is t=
hought, will increase the price of Bitcoin.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If your interest in crypto is =E2=80=9Cnumber =
go up,=E2=80=9D this is good. If your interest in crypto is =E2=80=9Cthis i=
s the financial system of the future and will increasingly be adopted by bi=
g institutions and ordinary people,=E2=80=9D this is a mixed bag: On the on=
e hand, there is a lot of optimism about ETF approval driving retail and in=
stitutional adoption; on the other hand, =E2=80=9Ceveryone owns Bitcoin thr=
ough a BlackRock ETF in their Fidelity brokerage account=E2=80=9D is not qu=
ite proof that crypto is the financial system of the future. If your intere=
st in crypto is =E2=80=9Ccrypto keeps coming up with fun new ways to do fin=
ance,=E2=80=9D though, this is pretty boring. Crypto=E2=80=99s fun new way =
to do finance is to put Bitcoin in a box and sell you shares of the box; th=
e goal is to transmute Bitcoin =E2=80=94=C2=A0this decentralized disinterme=
diated trustless novel form of money that was meant to replace the banks an=
d brokerages=C2=A0=E2=80=94=C2=A0into regular stocks.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway while you wait for the ETF, <a href=3D"=
https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33892453.286409/aHR0cHM6Ly93d=
3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDEtMDQvZXgtY2l0aS1leGVjcy1w=
