<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A lot of innovations in crypto have two separa=
te but related rationales:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">This thing is the future of human soc=
iety!</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">This thing avoids securities=
 law!</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I remember when blockchains were touted=C2=A0b=
oth=C2=A0as a new way to keep track of all of the world=E2=80=99s informati=
on and also, somehow, a way around securities law: If you put stock on the =
blockchain, the theory went, the US Securities and Exchange Commission coul=
dn=E2=80=99t regulate it. (This theory has fallen out of favor, but <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33892453.286409/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDctMTQvcmlwcGxlLWlz=
LWEtc2VjdXJpdHktYW5kLWl0LWlzbi10P2NtcGlkPUJCRDAxMDQyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9=
tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDEwNCZ1dG1fY2=
FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB2e3be12b" itemprop=3D"Sto=
ryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; =
text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-c=
olor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> not en=
tirely</a>.)=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Or=C2=A0people in crypto have <a href=3D"https=
://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33892453.286409/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYm=
xvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTYtMDUtMTcvYmxvY2tjaGFpbi1jb21wY=
W55LXdhbnRzLXRvLXJlaW52ZW50LWNvbXBhbmllcz9jbXBpZD1CQkQwMTA0MjRfTU9ORVlTVFVG=
RiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yNDAxMDQ=
mdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB9fb6325f" itempro=
p=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #=
000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-=
bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"=
> spent years arguing</a> that decentralized autonomous organizations are a=
 new and better way to organize economic activity, never seen before. (This=
 is wrong and <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/3389=
2453.286409/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjM=
tMTAtMjQvYmlnLWJvbnVzZXMtYXJlLWJhY2stYXQtdWstYmFua3M_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDEwNDI0X0=
1PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlc=
m09MjQwMTA0JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB2c1383=
b8" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-c=
olor: #ccc;"> they are general partnerships</a>, but never mind.) But there=
 are also sometimes arguments=C2=A0that DAOs are a way around securities re=
gulation: If some crypto project (a decentralized exchange, a lending platf=
orm, whatever) is run by a DAO rather than by a company, then it is more ro=
bust to regulation; regulators can=E2=80=99t fine the DAO or arrest its lea=
ders, because it is decentralized and computerized and thus resistant to go=
vernment interference.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">My guess is that this is partly correct: Some =
decentralized crypto projects really do run as more or less autonomous code=
 on distributed blockchains and really=C2=A0<em>can=E2=80=99t=C2=A0</em>be =
shut down by an SEC order.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-4" =
style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wi=
dth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !importan=
t; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[4]</span>
</a>=C2=A0But there do seem to be a lot of <a href=3D"https://link.mail.blo=
ombergbusiness.com/click/33892453.286409/aHR0cHM6Ly94a2NkLmNvbS81Mzgv/607f0=
7ceef4b8524a319a23cB8fda4932" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope=
" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importa=
nt; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-s=
tyle: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> $5 wrench vulnerabilities</a> in cry=
pto, where =E2=80=9Cdecentralized autonomous organization=E2=80=9D is a fan=
cy way of saying =E2=80=9CDiscord page for voting on stuff,=E2=80=9D and th=
e SEC can find the Discord=E2=80=99s administrator and say =E2=80=9Chey we =
can make your life bad if you don=E2=80=99t shut down this DAO=E2=80=9D and=
 the administrator shuts it down and everything was a lot less decentralize=
d and autonomous and organized than people thought.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Last month the SEC <a href=3D"https://link.mai=
l.bloombergbusiness.com/click/33892453.286409/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZ=
XdzL3ByZXNzLXJlbGVhc2UvMjAyMy0yNTg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd0554c76" itemp=
rop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color:=
 #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; borde=
r-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc=
;"> shut down a DAO</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Securities and Exchange Commission [Dec. 2=
2] announced that BarnBridge DAO, a purportedly decentralized autonomous or=
ganization, and its two founders, Tyler Ward and Troy Murray, will pay more=
 than $1.7 million to settle charges that they failed to register BarnBridg=
e=E2=80=99s offer and sale of structured crypto asset securities known as S=
MART Yield bonds. The Commission also charged the respondents with violatio=
ns stemming from operating BarnBridge=E2=80=99s SMART Yield pools as unregi=
stered investment companies. To settle the SEC=E2=80=99s charges, BarnBridg=
e agreed to disgorge nearly $1.5 million of proceeds from the sales, and Wa=
rd and Murray each agreed to pay a $125,000 civil penalties.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CThe use of blockchain technology for =
the unregistered offer and sale of structured finance products to retail in=
vestors runs afoul of the securities laws," said Gurbir S. Grewal, Director=
 of the SEC=E2=80=99s Division of Enforcement. "This case serves as an impo=
rtant reminder that those laws apply to all who wish to access our capital =
markets, regardless of whether they are, or purport to be, incorporated, de=
centralized or autonomous.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Reading <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/33892453.286409/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9maWxlcy9saXRp=
Z2F0aW9uL2FkbWluLzIwMjMvMzMtMTEyNjIucGRm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB94b12f55"=
 itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"=
color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px;=
 border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color=
: #ccc;"> the SEC order</a>, it is a little puzzling how BarnBridge could h=
ave settled the case. It=E2=80=99s a DAO? Did it, like, take a vote? Appare=
ntly not; apparently the SEC got to the founders and the founders shut it d=
own:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In July 2023, Ward and Murray took=
 steps to close investments in a second version of SMART Yield that had lau=
nched in January 2023, after BarnBridge DAO had stopped offering investment=
s in SMART Yield Pools described in this Order. Ward and Murray also cancel=
ed a new product launch, limited access to Discord, Github, and other platf=
orms used by BarnBridge DAO, and stopped development of further securities =
using the BarnBridge protocol.</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So not=C2=A0<em>that </em>decentralized or aut=
onomous.</p>
