which is a way of exchanging your voting rights (which you don=E2=80=99t ca=
re about) for money (in the form of stock lending fees).</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But I guess the most obvious solution is just,=
 like, go around paying retail shareholders for their votes? With some inte=
